Meru woman MP Kawira Mwangaza on Monday recorded a statement with the police on the charge of attacking a journalist. The woman representative staged a scene at the Milimani law courts after confiscating Weru TV's Boniface Mwongera's phone. She accused the journalist of taking pictures during the proceedings of a case where she has sued a musician for defamation. Mwongera was covering the proceedings and had sent the pictures to a newsroom WhatsApp group. The MP recorded a statement at the Capitol Hill police station. She took the phone with her. She later proceeded to the Cybercrime Department offices at the DCI headquarters with the device. The journalist also recorded his statement over the incident and accused Mwangaza of insulting him. Police said they are still investigating the matter to determine whether to charge the lawmaker. Click here for the latest political news